uld confirm if Scala 3 handles Java varargs appropriately and whether `Array.emptyByteArray` exists.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Verifying empty byte array**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether `Array.emptyByteArray` exists in Scala 2 or 3. It seems that Predef might have it, but I'm not entirely sure. To be safer, I think I should use `Array.empty[Byte]` instead. That way, it feels more consistent and reliable. It might be a good idea to edit my approach to ensure clarity, as relying on potentially ambiguous constructs could lead to confusion later on. Let's make that adjustment!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_WawKi0yaGAv6PMxvQq5A1uYu|fc_0be9edce1c5e5bcf0169f7a5d71dbc81a1b97777afeddb99da\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-protobuf-v3_3/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_protobuf_v3_3/GeneratedMessageLiteInnerSerializedFormTest.scala\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"  @static val DEFAULT_INSTANCE: SerializedFormModernLiteMessage = new SerializedFormModernLiteMessage(Array.emptyByteArray)\", \"newText\": \"  @static val DEFAULT_INSTANCE: SerializedFormModernLiteMessage = new SerializedFormModernLiteMessage(Array.empty[Byte])\"}, {\"oldText\": \"  @static val defaultInstance: SerializedFormLegacyLiteMessage = new SerializedFormLegacyLiteMessage(Array.emptyByteArray)\", \"newText\": \"  @static val defaultInstance: SerializedFormLegacyLiteMessage = new SerializedFormLegacyLiteMessage(Array.empty[Byte])\"}, {\"oldText\": \"  private var bytes: Array[Byte] = Array.emptyByteArray\", \"newText\": \"  private var bytes: Array[Byte] = Array.empty[Byte]\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    bytes = Array.emptyByteArray\", \"newText\": \"    bytes = Array.empty[Byte]\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 604, \"output\": 746, \"cacheRead\": 29184, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 30534, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"o